<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2,img,p { margin:0; } p {margin-bottom: 10px;}</mj-style>
    <!-- <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" /> -->
    <mj-font
      name="Roboto+Serif"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap"
    />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f9f8f9">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section
      background-color="#eff1f4"
      css-class="border-line"
      padding="1px 0.5px 1px 1px"
      border-radius="5px"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" border-radius="5px" padding="0px">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px"
          css-class="light_img"
          width="150px"
          src="https://www.businesshistory.co/logo-gray.png"
          href="https://www.businesshistory.co"
          alt=""
        />

        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 10px"
        />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Every successful company has a turning point—a risk that paid off, a
            product that redefined an industry, or a decision that changed
            everything. However, not every story is one of triumph; some of the
            most valuable lessons come from the failures and missteps that
            shaped the business landscape.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <!-- <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" /> -->
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <mj-section
      background-color="#eff1f4"
      css-class="border-line"
      padding="1px 0.5px 1px 1px"
      border-radius="5px"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" border-radius="5px" padding="0px">
        <mj-text
          padding="16px 12px 0px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="white"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              color: #8c3321;
              text-align: left;
              border-bottom: 2px solid #8c3321;
              font-size: 26px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              padding-bottom: 8px;
            "
          >
            The Internet made everyone get these viral products
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-spacer height="18px"></mj-spacer>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            Fire meets PR
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The viral Stanley Cup is a product from a company that was founded
            way back in 1913. Stanley has always been known for its rugged,
            steel-insulated gear, which workers and campers used. However, the
            well-renowned
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #8c3321;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-02-08-2025-40-oz-quencher-tumbler?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >40 oz Quencher tumbler</a
            >
            was launched in 2016 and flopped big time. It didn’t perform well in
            traditional retail, and trade was so poor that it was nearly
            discontinued.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px 14px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/lainey-wilson-watermelon-moonshine-quencher-collab.jpg"
          alt="The brand launched its first celebrity collaboration with the country musician Lainey Wilson, who produced a pink-and-green Watermelon Moonshine Quencher"
          href="https://www.businesshistory.co"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              The brand launched its first collaboration with the country
              musician Lainey Wilson, who produced a pink-and-green Watermelon
              Moonshine Quencher. Credits: Getty Images</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Then came the moment that set the internet ablaze. A
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #8c3321;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-02-08-2025-tiktok-video?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >TikTok video</a
            >
            went viral in 2023 featuring a woman whose Kia Sorento had been
            destroyed in a car fire. Everything in the car was reduced to ash
            except her Stanley Quencher. The company’s CEO posted a response
            acknowledging the video and offering to get the woman a car. His
            post was widely applauded online, and suddenly, Stanley gained
            traction and eventually became iconic.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Stanley capitalized on the hype by targeting TikTok moms and
            influencers. When women said, "<i>We love this cup and here’s why</i
            >," the brand pivoted and provided exactly what the customer wanted
            and more. They focused on exclusive color drops, social media
            engagement, and scarcity-based hype.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            Currently, Stanley has grown into a nearly $ 750M annual business,
            up from around $70–94M in 2019–2020.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>
